-- Yunel Escobar of Blue Jays Banned Three Games for Anti-Gay Slur
-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 2012-09-18T19:36:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-18/yunel-escobar-of-blue-jays-banned-three-games-for-anti-gay-slur.html
Yunel Escobar of the Toronto Blue Jays was suspended for three games after he wore eye-black patches bearing an anti-gay slur in Spanish.  The ban was announced in a news release from the Blue Jays, who open a Major League Baseball series against the  New York  Yankees at Yankee Stadium tonight.  To contact the editor responsible for this story: Larry Siddons at   lsiddons@bloomberg.net  